trans-unit.source: checks can be registered with a ttl instead of a script and interval this means that the service will check in with the agent before the ttl expires. If it doesn't the check will be considered failed. Required if registering a check and the script an interval are missing Similar to the interval this is a number with a s or m suffix to signify the units of seconds or minutes e.g 15s or 1m. If no suffix is supplied, m will be used by default e.g. 1 will be 1m
trans-unit.target: 支票可以使用ttl而不是脚本和间隔进行注册，这意味着服务将在ttl到期之前通过代理进行签入。如果没有，则检查将被视为失败。如果注册支票且脚本缺少间隔，则为必填项。与间隔类似，这是一个后缀为as或m的数字，表示秒或分钟的单位，例如 15s 或 1m 。如果没有提供后缀，则默认情况下将使用 m ，例如 1 将为 1m
